cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SI, cs.DS

The paper proposes a novel generative model for learning multiple graphs from mixture data. This involves clustering a set of data and learning a graph for each cluster. The paper focuses on graph learning methods and their application to datasets, which suggests that the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves generative models, which could also place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The experiments involve both synthetic and real-world datasets, which could suggest cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper deals with clustering and learning, which could also place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
